Order Administrator (1 year Contract) (FISHER/201402/03/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00006751
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Feb 19 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Enter customer orders into Business Management systems – Order Processing System (OPS)/IBM and JDE.
Review incoming orders (commercial) according to established guidelines.
Execute order processing activities related to pricing, discounts, commission, change order etc. according to established guidelines.
Ensure accuracy of data entry in OPS transactions, JDE, Bookings and Sales.
Prioritize orders to achieve targets and on time processing and provide timely response to order enquiries.
Update order status in the order management system.
Coordinate/liaise with Sales offices, factories and internal functions to resolve problems associated with orders.
Requirements:
Diploma/NITEC in Business Management or equivalent; GCE ‘O’ level with relevant experience will be considered.
1 to 2 years experience with knowledge of commercial terms and conditions.
Good interpersonal, written and verbal communication skills.
Proficient in MS Office applications and preferably with exposure to ERP systems (SAP/JDE).